# Naming conventions

Apply these conventions throughout the project.

- Use `kebab-case` for filenames.
- Use `PascalCase` for classes, interfaces, types, enums, and type aliases.
- Use `camelCase` for functions, methods, variables, parameters, and object properties.

## Code examples

```ts
export class PDFDocument {}
export class Renderer {}
export function renderTable() {}
```

## Related files

Use the same lowercase base name with a descriptive suffix:

```text
renderer.ts
renderer.helpers.ts
renderer.test.ts
renderer.types.ts
renderer.constants.ts
renderer.factory.ts
```

Keep filenames lowercase. Use dots to separate the base filename from a clear role suffix.
